tuwunel-description =
    Tuwunel is a fast, lightweight Matrix homeserver written in Rust.

    It supports the full Matrix specification including federation with other
    homeservers, OIDC-native authentication via Kanidm, end-to-end encrypted
    messages, and all Matrix room types.

    Tuwunel is the successor to conduwuit and is designed for low-resource
    self-hosted deployments.

tuwunel-features =
    - Full Matrix federation
    - OIDC authentication via Kanidm (no separate password database)
    - End-to-end encryption
    - Voice and video calls (via Matrix TURN)
    - Low memory footprint
    - RocksDB storage backend
